Within and beyond our six counties, we have partnered with more than 105 educational service providers in 62 Ohio counties, 39 states and Canada.

details: The primary purpose of St. Bridget of Kildare Preschool program is to provide a transition from home to a school atmosphere. While recognizing that family relationships provide the young child with the best model for developing attitudes, values and appropriate behavior. The St. Bridget of Kildare Preschool program offers other children and adults in and atmosphere of Christian love and concern. The preschool program promotes the spiritual, intellectual, social, and physical growth of the young child in a creative learning environment through age appropriate development experiences and play activities.

name: SAINT JOHN SCHOOL
details: Saint John School is the PreK-12 Catholic educational institution serving the Diocese of Youngstown in Ashtabula, Lake and Geauga counties. Within a rich and diverse community of faith, students are prepared to be Heralds of the gospel bringing light and truth to others. Our academic program provides students with the knowledge and skills to be prepared for futher education and learning in the 21st century. In partnership with families and the Catholic Community, Saint John School instills in its graduates the values of character, service and leadership.

name: SALEMTOWNSHIP ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: Salem Elementary operates as a K-4 building. Our highest priority is to attain student growth in all grade levels. We look forward to getting to know our students and families as we progress through the year. Please do not hesitate to contact us should you have any questions or concerns.

name: SAM SALEM COMMUNITY LEARNING CENTER
details: Thank you for choosing Sam Salem Community Learning Center for the very important job of educating your student.  Our excellent faculty and staff work hard everyday to deliver the highest quality of instruction to meet the needs of each student.  By providing a safe learning environment and recognizing positive behaviors and choices of students, we carry-out our mission statement every day. The mission statement of Sam Salem Community Learning Center is to ensure that each student achieves their lifelong potential in a safe environment.

name: SANDS MONTESSORI ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: Sands Montessori School's mission is to provide a culturally integrated quality education for each child using Maria Montessori's method and her philosophy of "Education for Life." We are committed to the development of the whole child fulfilling his/her intellectual, social, spiritual and physical needs. The success of our mission will be strengthened by the establishment of a partnership among child, school community and family. It is our ultimate goal to prepare each child to become a citizen of the world.

name: SANDY VALLEY SCHOOL
details: The mission of the Sandy Valley Local School District is to provide a quality education to all students through the cooperative efforts of the schools, parents and community. Each student, regardless of achievement or ability level, is to be prepared for success in his or her chosen endeavors.

name: SARDINIA SCHOOL
details: It is the mission of Sardinia Elementary that, in an atmosphere of mutual respect, our students will be provided with a safe and nurturing environment. We expect each student to master the basic academic skills to the best of his/her ability. We will guide them to explore and discover the knowledge necessary to make good choices throughout life: thereby aiding our students to become literate, productive, creative, and responsible members of a global society.

name: SAVILLE ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: Our faculty and staff work hard to provide all students with the tools to become productive, responsible citizens. Our goal is to prepare students for life in the 21st century by providing both the vital knowledge and skills that they need while at the same time encouraging creativity, problem solving, collaboration communications, and curiosity. We believe the responsibility for learning is shared by students, teachers and parents.

name: SAYLER PARK ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: Sayler Park School is a neighborhood school and Community Learning Center where students reach their full potential through project-based learning. Our students build leadership skills and confidence as they work alongside community members to solve real-world challenges.

name: SCARLET OAKS CDC
details: Great Oaks specializes in career and technical education for both high school students and adults. At four campuses, Great Oaks high school students prepare for careers and college, and adults get training and certification to begin a new career or advance in a current career.

name: SCHOOL OF BRIGHT PROMISE
details: We, at the School of Bright Promise & the Jefferson Regional Spectrum Center are committed to empowering and supporting students by meeting their individual needs to encourage and support their full potential.  Students will demonstrate self-reliance and respectful citizenship skills; and they will contribute to their community by working with parents and teachers to become productive members of society.

name: SCHOOL OF HOPE
details: Our mission is to provide every individual student the opportunity to participate in learning activities, work training, volunteering, and social/community experiences to the fullest extent possible.

name: SCHULTE
details: On behalf of the teachers, support staff, administration, and the Board of Education, we welcome you to an educational opportunity of a lifetime! You will experience a transformation of your definition of school and learning. Through the efforts of our highly qualified staff, you will be presented concepts of the world of work, such as technical abilities, academic skills, and employability skills. Mastery of these concepts will be the basis of your success at the Scioto County Career Technical Center and your success through life.

name: SCHUMACHER CLC AFTER SCHOOL PROGRAM
details: The mission of Schumacher CLC is to educate all students to their highest potential involving the collaboration of educators, parents, and the community

name: SCIOTO DARBY ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: Scioto Darby is a K-5 Elementary school located within the Hilliard City School District in central Ohio.

name: SCIOTO ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: The mission of Teays Valley Schools is to educate and encourage each student to lead a productive life

name: SCIOTO RIDGE ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: As Scioto Ridge citizens, we pledge to be leaders!

name: SCIOTOVILLE ELEMENTARY ACADEMY
details: Together we will learn as much as we can everyday to be responsible, respectful, and successful.

name: SCOTTWOOD ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: Our Mission: Each student is highly educated, prepared for leadership and service, and empowered for success as a citizen in a global community.

name: SCRANTON SCHOOL
details: Scranton is a highly effective PreK-8 school located on the West side near Tremont and Ohio City. We are staffed to serve a diverse population of young scholars, including a strong bilingual program. Our academic performance has steadily increased over the past five years. Scranton earned "A" ratings in all areas of value-added on the Ohio State Report Card, meaning that our scholars earned more than one year's worth of academic growth in 1 school year. Many of our classrooms are equipped with Smart boards, Elmo document cameras and computers in order to enhance each child's academic experience. Scranton is also equipped with a full computer lab that is used by all grade levels for the implementation of programs such as Study Island, Imagine Learning, ABC Mouse, First in Math and Accelerated Reader. We currently have 3 preschool classrooms, 1 full day and two half day.

name: SEABORN ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: We believe it is the duty and responsibility of each student, parent, and staff member to develop and project a feeling of cooperation, interest, and respect for the Seaborn Elementary School community.
